---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout title="Ed Barlow — Ed Barlow">
  <section class="home-intro">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <h1 class="home-name">Ed Barlow</h1>
      <div class="home-body">
<h2>Current Project:  The GAME Framework for Agentic Development</h2>
<p>I am combining my <a href="https://www.amazon.com/Process-Based-Database-Administration-Management-ebook/dp/B073RRQBZC">Process Based Methodology</a> and scale-proven <a href="https://webcloudstudio.github.io/webcloudstudio/project-docs/Specifications/Features.html">Technology Rules</a> into a 
Framework for development that seamlessly enables enterprise capabilities and enables capability sharing within a workgroup (family or team)</p>
<p>The concept is exciting.  Contact me if you want to collaborate.</p>
<p>Key Concept: An Agent will conform your code projects.  This means adding annotations and new scripts to expose your capabilities of your projects.  capability exposure is done
with minimal impact.  I use an Agent to make all your code look the same.</p>
<p>Key Concept: This can also enforce best practices, your branding, and security and other rules across all your projects</p>
<p>Key Concept: If my Capability Catalog knows how to run everything on your machine, we can advertise those capabilities through our workgroup</p>
<p>Key Concept: Your agents can use these discovered capabilities in an MCP like manner - but from your python with no token</p>
<p>Key Concpet: Might as well give you a full user interface... so i did...  Not done but Logging/Monitorng/Scheduling/Verification ... </p>
<h3>The GAME Framework contains</h3>
<ul>
<li>A <strong>Control Panel</strong> provides namespaced unified views (namespaced) of your projects.</li>
<li>A <strong>Capability Catalog</strong> to provide capabilities and share resources (transport agnostic: Rest, CLI, Async, MCP)</li>
<li>A <strong>A Prototyper Workflow</strong> with agents providing and ensuring consistent builds</li>
<li><strong>Simple Workflow</strong> based project management and namespaced project organization</li>
<li><strong>Enterprise Operations</strong> - Monitoring, Documentation, Scheduled tasks, and Data Flows and <strong>Sharing</strong></li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Hands On Backend Technology Leader</strong> at hedge funds, investment banks, insurance companies, and startups </p>
<p><strong>Author</strong>, <strong>Speaker</strong>, <strong>Free Software Developer</strong></p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <style>
    .home-intro { padding: 4rem 0 3rem; }

    .home-name {
      font-size: clamp(2.5rem, 5vw, 4rem);
      font-weight: 800;
      letter-spacing: -0.02em;
      margin: 0 0 2rem;
    }

    .home-body { max-width: 860px; }

    .home-body p {
      font-size: 1.05rem;
      color: var(--muted);
      line-height: 1.75;
      margin: 0 0 1.25rem;
    }

    .home-body h2 {
      font-size: 1.1rem;
      font-weight: 700;
      color: var(--text);
      margin: 2rem 0 0.75rem;
      letter-spacing: 0.01em;
    }

    .home-body ul {
      list-style: none;
      padding: 0;
      margin: 0 0 1.25rem;
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
      gap: 0.5rem;
    }

    .home-body li {
      font-size: 0.95rem;
      color: var(--muted);
      padding-left: 1.2rem;
      position: relative;
    }

    .home-body li::before {
      content: '—';
      position: absolute;
      left: 0;
      color: var(--accent);
    }

    .home-body strong { color: var(--text); font-weight: 600; }

    .home-body em {
      color: var(--muted);
      font-style: italic;
      font-size: 0.92rem;
    }
  </style>
</Layout>
